MOST IMMEDIATE
No.1/34/1/2017-Cab.
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 18th May, 2017
The undersigned is directed to say that consequent upon the demise of Shri Anil Madhav
Dave, Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate
Change on the 18h May, 2017, Dr. Harsh Vardhan assumed the charge of the office of the Minister
of Environment, Forest and Climate Change. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the
Minister of Science and Technology; and Minister of Earth Sciences.
(S.G.P. Verghese)
